  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Analysis of barriers in psoriasis care from the patient's and the physician's perspective and
      generation of scientific data on the quality of health care in Denmark, Poland, Spain, United
      Kingdom, and Germany
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Cross-sectional, non-interventional study on healthcare for psoriasis in patients and their
      treating physicians. Clinical data on severity as well as subjective estimates on disease
      burden, quality of life etc. will be collected. Data collection is planned at multiple,
      representative sites in five European countries with different healthcare systems with the
      aim to identify system-dependent and -independent barriers in guideline-compliant psoriasis
      care.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
